Bombardier profits fall as aircraft deliveries and orders decline
Bombardier Inc., a Canadian aircraft and rail manufacturer, reported a 15 percent drop in net profit on Thursday, amid pressure from lower orders and aircraft deliveries in the third quarter and contract problems in its Trains division.
Montreal-based Bombardier also did not provide in-flight test data for its all-new CSeries aircraft or information on whether the aircraft will meet its ambitious timeline for commercial commissioning before next September.
