We believe Bombardier will register new orders for its CSeries aircraft as the in-flight test program progresses.
However, if no new orders are announced in the coming months, we expect the market to become more skeptical about the program.
Bombardier hopes that the CSeries family of aircraft will be able to catapult it into the lower segment of a market now dominated by Boeing and Airbus.
The first test aircraft was unveiled in March and flew for the first time in September after months of delay.
But the number of firm orders for CSeries aircraft has so far been modest at 177. It appears that potential buyers are waiting for the results of flight tests to validate the company's claims regarding energy efficiency and the savings potential of the new airliner.
