This will happen again throughout the flight program.
The second of the five test aircraft is expected to depart in the coming weeks, the others will follow shortly thereafter, the company said.
Still, analysts are skeptical that the first customer could fly a CSeries aircraft just 12 months after its maiden flight.
Bombardier said it is assessing the entry into service schedule and will provide new information in the coming months.
